<div style="text-align: center; max-width: 500px; margin: 0 auto; font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;">
    <img src="https://polygol.github.io/assets/appicon/feedback.png" style="width: 64px; height: 64px; margin-bottom: 20px; border-radius: 50%;">
    <h1 style="margin: 0 0 10px 0; font-weight: 600;">Customization</h1>
    <p style="opacity: 0.8; font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.5; margin-bottom: 30px;">
        Make Polygol yours. The environment adapts to your style.
    </p>

    <div style="text-align: left; margin-bottom: 30px;">
        <h3 style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Wallpapers</h3>
        <p style="opacity: 0.8; margin-bottom: 15px;">
            Open Controls and select Wallpaper to upload images or videos. If you upload multiple files, they will automatically play as a slideshow.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Clock Styles</h3>
        <p style="opacity: 0.8; margin-bottom: 15px;">
            Change the font, weight, color, and size of the clock directly from the Controls menu. You can even create a stacked layout.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-bottom: 10px;">Widgets</h3>
        <p style="opacity: 0.8; margin-bottom: 15px;">
            Polygol supports a simple weather widget that appear automatically when needed. Toggle them in Controls.
        </p>
    </div>

    <button onclick="minimizeWindowEmbed(); document.getElementById('persistent-clock').click();" style="
        padding: 12px 24px; 
        border-radius: 20px; 
        background: var(--search-background); 
        color: var(--text-color); 
        border: 1px solid var(--glass-border); 
        font-size: 1rem; 
        font-weight: 500; 
        cursor: pointer; 
        display: inline-flex; 
        align-items: center; 
        gap: 8px;
        font-family: 'Inter';">
        Try customization
    </button>
</div>